   {
      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "LTO has historically be a source of bugs in compilers - it's improved a lot of course, and we should evaluate when it's mature enough to enable. But that's a far bigger change than enabling link-time GC.\r\n\r\nIn addition, experiments in the past have shown that LTO wasn't always a performance gain (it has been a while, the situation may be better now, but even then, maybe we only want it for certain compiler versions etc...).",
